In our previous work [5] this kind of theorem led to the following (conditional) result: Theorem 3.2 (Conditional) On Hypothesis A, each of the constants , log 2, (3) is 2-normal.
Also, on Hypothesis A, if (5) be irrational then it likewise is 2-normal.
Theorem 3.2 works, of course, because the indicated fundamental constants admit of polylogarithm-like expansions of the form rn b-n where rn is rational-polynomial.
