For a different research foray, consider the problem of specifying an uncountable collection of normals.
One way to do this is surprisingly easy.
In what follows we define the bits of a real number according to the no-trailer rule: Any infinite trailer of 1's is to be removed via carry; e.g., 0.01111 ... 0.1 in binary; and then when we ask for the k -th bit of a real number in [0, 1) we shall mean the k -bit to the right of the decimal point.
