The expectation E of the gap-maximum can be obtained by direct integration of this distribution formula, to yield: 1 E (GN ) = ( (N +1)+ ) N where is the standard polygamma function /.
Thus for large N we have log N + - 1/2 1 + O( 2 ) N N log N .
N This shows that whereas the mean gap is 1/N , the mean maximum gap is essentially (log N )/N .
In this sense, which remains heuristic with an uncertain implication for our problem, we expect a high-order cascaded PRNG to have gaps no larger than "about" (log P )/P where P is the overall period of the PRNG.
It turns out that for very specialized PRNGs we can effect rigorous results on the gap-maximum GN .
